WEBVTT

00:12.595 --> 00:13.596
[birds chirping]

00:13.680 --> 00:16.683
[goats bleating]

00:26.860 --> 00:28.903
[creaking]

00:32.949 --> 00:34.576
[men panting]

00:35.118 --> 00:37.495
[whinnies]

00:51.926 --> 00:52.969
[panting]

00:55.638 --> 00:56.848
Shh, shh. Hey, hey...

00:57.766 --> 00:58.975
[Kiki in Spanish]
Drop the gun.

01:06.566 --> 01:09.277
[panting]

01:10.737 --> 01:13.156
[goats bleating]

01:16.076 --> 01:18.036
[gunshots from a distance]

01:19.245 --> 01:20.080
[door creaks]

01:20.163 --> 01:22.582
[man 1 in Spanish]
Hey, don't move! Don't move!

01:23.083 --> 01:24.250
Cuff him!

01:25.085 --> 01:27.045
-Clear?
-[officer] Yes. All clear!

01:27.128 --> 01:31.007
Gentlemen. Clear!
Let's bring it down. Let's go!

01:32.050 --> 01:33.551
[officer 2] Let's go.

01:33.635 --> 01:37.305
[in English] Wow. These guys, uh...
they didn't put up much of a fight.

01:37.388 --> 01:38.223
[chuckles]

01:38.306 --> 01:39.307
How much, you think?

01:39.390 --> 01:42.519
[man 2] 250 pounds.
Not more. Maybe a little less.

01:42.602 --> 01:44.145
Same as they give us every month.

01:44.854 --> 01:45.814
So this is a set-up?

01:47.107 --> 01:48.483
It's more like a donation.

01:48.566 --> 01:50.944
Locals get a win,
a little piece of the action.

01:51.402 --> 01:52.445
Everyone's happy.

01:53.863 --> 01:55.573
[horse whinnies]

01:55.657 --> 01:58.118
[snorting]

01:58.201 --> 02:00.703
Poor fella.
I'm gonna see if I can calm him down.

02:00.787 --> 02:01.621
[horse whinnies]

02:03.706 --> 02:05.041
Butch is a horse man.

02:07.502 --> 02:09.212
[man 3]
More of a ladies man myself.

02:16.928 --> 02:20.223
[officers chattering in Spanish]

02:25.311 --> 02:27.939
[indistinct chattering over radio]

02:38.449 --> 02:39.367
[man 2] Kiki.

02:39.909 --> 02:41.202
Come look at this.

02:44.914 --> 02:46.749
Entry wounds are at least a day old.

02:47.250 --> 02:49.419
But our friend the captain says
that they just shot them

02:49.502 --> 02:50.920
when they were trying to escape.

02:51.004 --> 02:53.548
Sounds like more fish stories for
the gringos.

02:54.090 --> 02:55.633
[man 1 in Spanish]
Excuse me.

02:55.717 --> 02:57.051
Go ahead, Captain.

02:59.304 --> 03:00.346
[sighs]

03:02.640 --> 03:04.184
[man 1 in English]
Recognize him, Jaime?

03:05.685 --> 03:06.728
Hernan Naranjo.

03:06.811 --> 03:09.355
He runs a lot of the Guadalajara trade.

03:09.439 --> 03:12.442
We found his brother dead yesterday at
the Hotel Americas.

03:12.525 --> 03:13.359
[in Spanish] Really?

03:14.903 --> 03:16.821
[in English] Someone's moving on
their territory?

03:19.407 --> 03:20.408
Let's walk.

03:25.788 --> 03:29.667
Yeah, there's not much rhyme or reason
in the pecking order around here, Kiki.

03:29.751 --> 03:33.087
Just backwood dirtbags
growing ditch weed on half an acre

03:33.171 --> 03:35.256
and every once in a while
killing each other.

03:35.340 --> 03:38.092
Best we can do is hold tight
and ride through the bullshit.

03:38.927 --> 03:40.178
Take what they give us.

03:40.970 --> 03:42.764
[horse whinnies]

03:42.847 --> 03:43.681
[gunshot]

03:47.268 --> 03:48.478
Motherfuckers.

03:50.688 --> 03:53.107
Sorry, bud.
Ain't like you could've rode her home.

03:53.650 --> 03:55.193
[car engine starts]

04:06.579 --> 04:09.415
[Rodrigo Amarante's "Tuyo" playing]

05:35.168 --> 05:37.170
[narrator] Life 101.

05:37.253 --> 05:41.132
All plants, even marijuana,
exist to make seeds.

05:41.215 --> 05:44.010
But sinsemilla flips that on its head.

05:44.177 --> 05:48.389
Starts with a female plant that flowers
without ever being pollinated.

05:48.473 --> 05:50.808
Kind of like the immaculate conception.

05:50.892 --> 05:54.062
But instead of baby Jesus,
you get bigger buds,

05:54.145 --> 05:55.980
packing more THC,

05:56.064 --> 05:59.484
making it the gold standard of
Mexican dope.

05:59.567 --> 06:02.362
But cross-pollination
can ruin an entire crop,

06:02.904 --> 06:06.741
so growing it outside is impossible
unless you're in the middle of a desert,

06:06.824 --> 06:08.743
which presents its own challenges...

06:09.202 --> 06:10.370
'cause it's a fucking desert.

06:11.746 --> 06:14.248
[man in Spanish]
Rafa, you have a call.

06:14.957 --> 06:16.501
They're dying, Cuco.

06:20.254 --> 06:21.339
They're waiting, brother.

06:24.967 --> 06:27.387
[norteño music playing]

06:29.555 --> 06:31.474
[explosion]

06:31.557 --> 06:34.227
Manuel! What are you doing, asshole?

06:34.310 --> 06:36.729
-Put that shit away.
-Yeah, Rafa.

06:36.813 --> 06:38.773
[Rafa]
What the fuck are you doing, idiot?

06:40.024 --> 06:42.485
We're growing the shit, not smoking it.

06:44.278 --> 06:45.738
Fucking weed.

06:54.622 --> 06:55.456
Yeah.

06:55.540 --> 06:58.918
-What's wrong with the weed?
-That geologist was full of shit.

07:00.670 --> 07:02.380
There's not enough water, Miguel.

07:02.463 --> 07:04.132
So find some, Rafael.

07:06.551 --> 07:09.220
We're setting up the biggest marijuana
distribution network

07:09.303 --> 07:10.638
in the history of Mexico.

07:11.264 --> 07:14.016
It won't mean shit if we don't have weed.

07:15.518 --> 07:16.727
Fix this, brother.

07:16.811 --> 07:18.020
[dial tone drones]

07:26.904 --> 07:28.030
This the pilot?

07:28.114 --> 07:30.408
Amado, my nephew.

07:31.742 --> 07:35.371
Has a good head on his shoulders.
Worked as a cop for awhile.

07:35.788 --> 07:37.165
Been helping me out.

07:37.957 --> 07:40.626
-Hey! You have a license?
-Sure, man.

07:41.335 --> 07:42.753
What kind you looking for?

07:44.005 --> 07:44.881
Let's go.

07:44.964 --> 07:46.549
How's the plantation?

07:46.841 --> 07:47.967
[Félix] Great.

07:49.802 --> 07:51.345
Weed up to your eyeballs.

07:52.096 --> 07:54.640
First Juárez,
then I'll tell you where's next.

07:59.353 --> 08:00.563
[engine starts]

08:01.647 --> 08:05.067
[narrator in English] Looking back,
even knowing how it all turned out,

08:05.151 --> 08:09.238
it's still hard to comprehend the scale
of Miguel Félix Gallardo's dream.

08:09.322 --> 08:10.823
The fucking audacity of it.

08:11.407 --> 08:15.286
But if you're gonna try, you need to know
that before the cartels existed,

08:15.369 --> 08:17.288
things worked differently in Mexico.

08:17.955 --> 08:20.458
The narcotics game was made
of lone wolf traffickers,

08:20.541 --> 08:23.336
mostly Sinaloans,
who purchased permission from the cops

08:23.419 --> 08:26.130
to run drugs
in a particular city or territory.

08:26.214 --> 08:27.048
MEXICO

08:27.131 --> 08:29.550
They called it the Plaza System.

08:29.634 --> 08:31.135
MEXICO CITY
GUADALAJARA

08:31.219 --> 08:32.637
Here's how it worked:

08:32.720 --> 08:34.931
Anyone looking to do business
in the territory

08:35.014 --> 08:36.432
had to cut in the plaza boss,

08:37.016 --> 08:39.101
pay him a piso, or a toll.

08:39.727 --> 08:44.273
And if they chose not to, trust me,
the boss made his displeasure known.

08:45.608 --> 08:48.569
But here's the key:
each plaza stood alone,

08:48.653 --> 08:51.322
was its own world,
run by a certified asshole

08:51.656 --> 08:55.201
who'd done enough dirt to get crowned
king of that particular piece of turf.

08:55.284 --> 08:57.537
The job tended to attract
hard motherfuckers.

08:57.620 --> 08:59.163
[grunting]

09:00.873 --> 09:03.960
So a scheme to convince
a bunch of rival plazas,

09:04.043 --> 09:07.296
led by trigger-happy sociopaths,
to work together,

09:07.380 --> 09:10.925
take direction from some other dirtbag?
Yeah, right.

09:11.008 --> 09:12.593
[in Spanish]
Good luck, friend.

09:14.804 --> 09:16.138
I mean it.

09:31.946 --> 09:34.156
[door opens]

09:34.240 --> 09:37.076
[in English] The baby's fine.
Mama needs a foot massage.

09:37.702 --> 09:38.536
Okay.

09:41.872 --> 09:43.374
[Kiki] We should find out the sex.

09:43.457 --> 09:46.085
It gives you a little time to
wrap your head around another boy.

09:46.168 --> 09:48.337
Oh, what makes you so sure
it's another boy?

09:49.547 --> 09:51.299
Oh, come on.

09:51.382 --> 09:53.426
Come on. I don't need to hear about
what a man you are

09:53.509 --> 09:55.303
and neither does our future daughter.

09:55.386 --> 09:56.220
[scoffs]

09:56.304 --> 09:58.472
I want to use the same formula
we gave Kikito.

10:00.433 --> 10:02.977
They can send it from Texas,
but it'll cost more.

10:05.271 --> 10:07.648
-You listening to me?
-Yeah.

10:08.024 --> 10:10.776
The doctors here are good
and the formula isn't.

10:10.860 --> 10:12.486
Oh, I missed my turn. Hold up.

10:14.780 --> 10:16.574
[horn honks]

10:28.502 --> 10:30.212
[gate creaks]

10:33.132 --> 10:35.009
[blinker ticking]

10:39.430 --> 10:40.598
[brakes screech softly]

10:41.098 --> 10:42.266
Where the hell are we?

10:42.892 --> 10:44.018
Uh...

10:44.769 --> 10:45.686
What are you doing?

10:45.770 --> 10:47.021
Hold up, hold on.

10:50.358 --> 10:51.901
Are you following someone?

10:51.984 --> 10:56.072
No, uh... Sears told me
that there's a good birria place nearby.

10:57.114 --> 10:59.200
I, uh... I must have heard wrong.

10:59.742 --> 11:01.911
Jesus, Kiki. On the way home from the OB?

11:02.703 --> 11:04.664
You never know when
you're gonna get lucky, right?

11:04.747 --> 11:08.000
Just don't get lucky when
you're picking up Kikito from school.

11:15.424 --> 11:17.301
[in Spanish]
Set the table for dinner.

11:18.469 --> 11:20.429
[in English]
Hey, that means make the table.

11:20.513 --> 11:22.598
[in Spanish]
We're going to speak more Spanish, Kikito.

11:23.140 --> 11:26.435
-[Kiki in English] Huh? Good luck.
-You're not staying for dinner?

11:26.519 --> 11:30.439
No, I gotta get back to the office, babe.
Kikito, where are your binoculars?

11:35.569 --> 11:36.612
Perfect.

11:36.696 --> 11:39.156
SCHOOL OF GEOLOGY

11:43.035 --> 11:45.037
[in Spanish]
And this is what makes the difference

11:45.121 --> 11:48.499
between permeable
and impermeable surfaces.

11:53.129 --> 11:54.338
Class is over.

11:57.091 --> 11:58.801
Didn't you hear, pussies?

11:58.884 --> 12:01.512
Get moving! Get the fuck out of here! Go!

12:01.595 --> 12:03.222
Fast. Move.

12:03.305 --> 12:04.807
[Cuco]
Come on. Let's go!

12:04.890 --> 12:07.685
Hurry up! Move it!

12:08.477 --> 12:10.479
Come on! Let's go!

12:12.440 --> 12:14.066
My babies are dying.

12:14.650 --> 12:16.068
Because of you, asshole.

12:18.863 --> 12:21.574
[man speaking Spanish on the radio]

12:45.973 --> 12:48.559
[car approaching]

13:01.614 --> 13:02.573
[in Spanish]
What's up?

13:03.240 --> 13:04.575
[Don Neto]
What's up, Pablo?

13:04.992 --> 13:06.577
Are the beers cold?

13:06.660 --> 13:07.745
[whistles]

13:09.497 --> 13:10.790
You look fatter, Don Neto.

13:11.791 --> 13:12.958
-[Don Neto] think so?
-Yeah.

13:13.501 --> 13:16.086
[Don Neto]
Problem in town?

13:18.005 --> 13:19.215
Nah, man.

13:19.298 --> 13:20.299
[horse whinnies]

13:28.974 --> 13:30.893
[Pablo]
You're proposing a monopoly.

13:30.976 --> 13:32.770
[Félix]
We're producing more than anyone else.

13:32.853 --> 13:36.106
With good distribution,
we'll dominate the market.

13:36.190 --> 13:39.193
Once we control it, we set a fixed price.

13:39.777 --> 13:40.778
Our price.

13:41.570 --> 13:45.032
On top of that, we don't have to
worry about getting undercut.

13:46.158 --> 13:47.952
More profits will come.

13:48.035 --> 13:50.746
And little by little, more stability.

13:50.830 --> 13:52.248
Hmm.

13:52.331 --> 13:54.208
Like how the Arabs do, right?

13:55.042 --> 13:57.545
OPEC for weed.

13:57.628 --> 13:59.338
[chuckles]

13:59.421 --> 14:02.633
There you go. More or less. [chuckles]

14:02.716 --> 14:05.469
And with control, there won't be violence.

14:07.054 --> 14:10.349
Only works if every plaza signs up.

14:10.432 --> 14:11.517
Yeah.

14:12.768 --> 14:15.980
We just need the important ones.
Most of them we know.

14:17.481 --> 14:20.150
-Sinaloans.
-Yeah.

14:20.234 --> 14:21.694
Like blondy here.

14:21.777 --> 14:23.529
Wandering motherfuckers.

14:23.612 --> 14:27.032
They're everywhere.
Fucking Jews of the mountains.

14:27.741 --> 14:31.078
No. We do business with any man
we trust and respect.

14:31.161 --> 14:34.456
Even if he's from a shit-stain
like Ojinaga.

14:34.540 --> 14:35.416
[horse neighs]

14:35.499 --> 14:39.879
-Hey! Don't pull too much! Slowly!
-Yes, boss.

14:40.462 --> 14:43.924
[Pablo] That nag cost me
a lot of fucking money, that asshole.

14:46.135 --> 14:47.344
You might have concerns.

14:48.470 --> 14:50.556
Why don't you come to our meeting
in Guadalajara?

14:50.639 --> 14:52.975
See what we can achieve together.

15:02.943 --> 15:06.614
You seem like a smart man, Miguel Ángel.
My problem is...

15:08.908 --> 15:09.867
your boss.

15:11.076 --> 15:12.411
He's not very smart.

15:14.246 --> 15:17.082
Pedro Avilés is not a man
you can do business with.

15:17.458 --> 15:21.086
We've had bad blood
over some bullshit for years.

15:23.714 --> 15:25.215
No, man.

15:26.550 --> 15:28.969
I don't think it would work.
I don't accept.

15:33.182 --> 15:36.060
I'm aware of your dispute. In fact...

15:36.518 --> 15:42.650
he asked me to let you know
he regrets his part in it.

15:44.693 --> 15:45.861
Look...

15:46.612 --> 15:48.238
those were his words.

15:49.031 --> 15:54.119
"Tell him that it's time to move forward."
That's what he said.

16:07.132 --> 16:10.511
I'll come to Guadalajara,
sit down with Avilés, the others.

16:10.928 --> 16:14.348
But if I don't see proof
you got the cops on board

16:14.431 --> 16:17.017
to grease this fucking OPEC thing?

16:19.687 --> 16:20.521
That'd be all.

16:21.271 --> 16:22.648
That's enough.

16:24.525 --> 16:25.818
Okay then, brother.

16:32.574 --> 16:33.409
That's nice.

16:34.076 --> 16:35.160
Nice, huh?

16:35.577 --> 16:38.789
-Does the date, too?
-Yeah.

16:39.873 --> 16:44.670
Actually, to celebrate the beginning
of this new venture, here you go.

16:45.879 --> 16:48.257
[chuckles]

16:49.675 --> 16:50.759
Check it out.

16:54.263 --> 16:55.889
[Pablo]
Like that, smooth.

16:56.348 --> 17:01.812
Like to be there when you tell Pedro
he has to kiss Acosta's dusty ass.

17:01.895 --> 17:03.272
What else could I do?

17:03.355 --> 17:05.524
You couldn't have told me
about the bad blood?

17:05.607 --> 17:09.028
I was sent to make introductions. You want
a history lesson, buy a fucking book.

17:09.111 --> 17:12.322
-You don't give a shit, do you?
-What's there to give a shit about?

17:12.823 --> 17:15.159
You know what this can be, for all of us.

17:15.325 --> 17:18.120
I also know when you start
moving furniture around,

17:18.203 --> 17:20.039
people stub their toes and get upset.

17:20.122 --> 17:21.415
We have to grow.

17:22.082 --> 17:24.960
Otherwise, life does
whatever the fuck it wants with you.

17:25.044 --> 17:26.628
It always does, sunshine.

17:27.004 --> 17:29.256
Fuck you, old man.

17:30.382 --> 17:31.258
Okay?

17:31.800 --> 17:33.677
Enough. Pick a side already.

17:37.389 --> 17:38.724
[chuckles]

17:54.656 --> 17:55.657
[camera clicks]

17:56.450 --> 17:57.826
[camera clicks]

17:59.244 --> 18:00.370
[camera clicks]

18:11.590 --> 18:15.219
[man]
So this super farm, it's ready?

18:15.969 --> 18:21.391
'Cause just laying irrigation in
would take months, no?

18:22.810 --> 18:23.727
Yeah.

18:25.604 --> 18:28.107
What Acosta doesn't know won't hurt him.

18:28.398 --> 18:29.650
You disagree?

18:29.733 --> 18:33.570
No. You got balls, man.

18:36.323 --> 18:38.867
-The watch was a cool touch.
-Right?

18:38.951 --> 18:40.661
-Yeah.
-Fake.

18:40.744 --> 18:42.204
[chuckles]

18:43.372 --> 18:48.460
So, enough weed to supply
the American market for a year.

18:51.004 --> 18:52.005
Right on.

18:54.258 --> 18:55.092
And then?

18:56.927 --> 18:57.761
What?

18:59.847 --> 19:03.433
You going to get all that product across
in trucks, or what?

19:03.517 --> 19:04.434
Yeah.

19:08.689 --> 19:09.606
Planes, man.

19:11.525 --> 19:12.776
A shitload of planes.

19:13.861 --> 19:15.195
That's the future.

19:15.279 --> 19:17.656
[Lola Beltrán's "El Mariachi" playing]

19:21.702 --> 19:24.955
[narrator in English] Félix's dream was
to create a union of Mexican traffickers.

19:25.038 --> 19:25.914
GUADALAJARA

19:25.998 --> 19:30.335
To make good on that, he had to sign up
enough bosses from the right plazas.

19:31.044 --> 19:34.381
And that meant convincing
some of the scariest dudes in Mexico

19:34.464 --> 19:36.091
to work together for once.

19:47.227 --> 19:48.604
Shit wasn't easy.

19:49.146 --> 19:52.941
But Félix grew up in Sinaloa.
He understood these guys.

19:53.483 --> 19:55.694
And he'd done his homework.

19:57.321 --> 19:59.907
That meant knowing which asshole
responded to flattery...

20:01.825 --> 20:04.536
and which just wanted to hear
the fucking numbers.

20:05.329 --> 20:09.291
But there was one thing each
and every one of them needed to know:

20:09.374 --> 20:13.128
That this idea of his was blessed
by the powers that be.

20:13.212 --> 20:15.380
'Cause without that in Mexico,
you got nothing.

20:15.464 --> 20:16.632
["El Mariachi" stops playing]

20:16.715 --> 20:19.676
[in Spanish] Tell your boss to come to
Guadalajara for the meeting.

20:19.760 --> 20:22.471
Our new partners want to make sure
the DFS is on board.

20:22.846 --> 20:26.850
The director will be there.
His time better not be wasted.

20:31.355 --> 20:32.189
Who is he?

20:32.272 --> 20:34.691
Nobody. Some ex-cop from Sinaloa.

20:36.276 --> 20:38.362
Smarter than the others, though.

20:41.907 --> 20:42.991
DIRECTORATE GENERAL

20:47.412 --> 20:50.624
[narrator in English] The official name
was the Federal Security Directorate,

20:50.707 --> 20:53.210
known in Mexico as the DFS.

20:53.710 --> 20:58.006
Their emblem was a tiger, 'cause why not?
Tigers are cool.

20:58.090 --> 21:00.259
[film narrator in Spanish]
The tiger is a powerful animal

21:00.342 --> 21:01.677
that doesn't fear danger.

21:01.760 --> 21:04.846
That's how an agent from the Federal
Security Directorate should be.

21:04.930 --> 21:08.850
[narrator in English] Came up with their
own anthem. Shit too weird to make up.

21:08.934 --> 21:10.811
[in Spanish]
♪ That's how an agent ♪

21:10.894 --> 21:14.815
♪ From the Federal
Security Directorate should be ♪

21:16.316 --> 21:18.860
[narrator in English] After World War II,
Mexico's new president

21:18.944 --> 21:21.113
was eager to attract U.S. investment,

21:21.196 --> 21:23.282
which meant picking a side
in the Cold War.

21:24.074 --> 21:27.786
To prove Mexico could get tough on Ivan,
the DFS was created,

21:27.869 --> 21:32.582
which basically meant if the CIA
needed shit done in Mexico, DFS did it.

21:33.125 --> 21:36.586
Tapping phones, keeping an eye
on Soviet and Cuban diplomats,

21:36.670 --> 21:40.841
and making sure any opposition
to the ruling PRI party was kept in check.

21:40.924 --> 21:42.634
Think Kent State was bad?

21:42.718 --> 21:46.263
When students gathered in 1968
to protest all the money being spent

21:46.346 --> 21:49.975
on the Mexico City Olympics,
the DFS showed up too...

21:50.267 --> 21:52.519
and killed hundreds of unarmed civilians.

21:52.602 --> 21:54.229
NIGHT OF HORROR IN TLATELOLCO!

21:54.313 --> 21:58.525
Apparently that qualified them to provide
security for visiting American diplomats.

21:59.276 --> 22:05.240
