29:45.742 --> 29:46.576
Hey, 'Mon!

29:47.535 --> 29:49.287
-Where you going?
-What?

29:49.370 --> 29:51.080
Pancho said I could get an ice cream.

29:51.164 --> 29:52.373
"Pancho said."

29:52.457 --> 29:55.794
Those TVs aren't gonna move themselves.
You're gonna get fat, little bastard.

29:56.461 --> 29:57.295
Come on, dude!

30:03.676 --> 30:05.887
So, partner with Pedro Avilés.

30:05.970 --> 30:07.305
Yeah.

30:07.764 --> 30:08.723
And we all get rich.

30:09.307 --> 30:13.478
No more blue jeans and toaster ovens.

30:13.561 --> 30:15.897
[chuckles]

30:15.980 --> 30:18.942
I'll talk to my brothers,
but I'm interested.

30:19.484 --> 30:21.110
If it's how you say.

30:21.528 --> 30:23.112
But only if it's cool with El Cubano.

30:24.864 --> 30:26.866
-Talking about Sicilia Falcón?
-[Benjamín] Yeah.

30:26.950 --> 30:30.119
He sells coke to movie stars.
What does he care?

30:30.203 --> 30:32.747
He made me and my brothers
welcome in Tijuana.

30:32.831 --> 30:34.582
I won't do anything that pisses him off.

30:35.124 --> 30:38.753
That's okay, bro. I'll speak with him,
make sure there's no misunderstandings.

30:39.754 --> 30:42.799
This isn't Sinaloa, man. Falcón's slick.

30:43.383 --> 30:45.134
He hangs with big shots. Connected people.

30:45.218 --> 30:48.972
I know someone who can arrange a meeting.
You can find people from Sinaloa anywhere.

31:04.696 --> 31:06.322
-Miguel Ángel.
-Hi.

31:06.823 --> 31:10.827
-It's been so long.
-Rodolfo's 18th birthday, I think.

31:11.744 --> 31:16.791
This is Ernesto Fonseca Carrillo,
and his nephew Amado.

31:17.000 --> 31:19.210
Amado Carrillo Fuentes. Pilot.

31:20.128 --> 31:22.714
Isabella Bautista. My pleasure.

31:25.049 --> 31:28.511
[Gerry Rafferty's "Baker Street" playing]

31:36.728 --> 31:38.354
[chattering]

32:14.349 --> 32:16.684
Hey. Is that Lucia Morales?

32:17.685 --> 32:19.562
-Yes.
-[laughing]

32:19.646 --> 32:21.356
She's going to sing for us later.

32:24.317 --> 32:26.319
Maybe you can tell her you're a pilot.

32:27.195 --> 32:28.363
Fuck, yeah.

32:29.364 --> 32:32.784
-Come on. I'll take you to meet Alberto.
-We'll be back.

32:37.914 --> 32:39.916
[Amado chuckles]

32:39.999 --> 32:41.584
[Amado]
All right. Good evening.

32:41.668 --> 32:45.046
[woman]
Cheers! Cheers, guys!

32:45.964 --> 32:47.966
You fit right in with these people.

32:48.466 --> 32:50.593
No. I'm good at pretending.

32:52.762 --> 32:54.430
Whoo! [laughs]

32:55.348 --> 32:59.978
-Rich people can't get enough of the shit.
-Yeah. They never get enough.

33:00.478 --> 33:02.939
[Isabella]
The margins are unbelievable.

33:07.819 --> 33:11.948
Juan Matta Ballesteros.
Owns the top airline in Honduras.

33:12.031 --> 33:15.827
Handles transportation for the Colombians.
Could introduce you.

33:16.536 --> 33:17.453
No.

33:18.162 --> 33:21.874
Cocaine's tricky.
It's still a niche business.

33:22.250 --> 33:25.670
Colombians only move real weight
through the Bahamas.

33:26.254 --> 33:28.548
But your Cuban friend, he's the real deal.

33:28.631 --> 33:31.592
-He must be doing something right.
-Yeah.

33:33.136 --> 33:35.972
Now it's our time to build an empire.

33:36.889 --> 33:38.182
Is that what we're doing?

34:00.496 --> 34:02.999
[Falcón in English]
It's okay, Tony. We are with friends.

34:03.499 --> 34:04.500
Hey, Tony.

34:04.834 --> 34:07.545
Tell Mr. Félix here how many men
you killed in Vietnam.

34:07.628 --> 34:09.047
[Tony]
Not enough, Mr. Falcón.

34:09.130 --> 34:10.923
[Falcón chuckles]

34:11.007 --> 34:12.508
[in Spanish]
He said "not enough."

34:12.592 --> 34:14.844
[laughs]

34:14.927 --> 34:16.429
Your home's very beautiful.

34:16.512 --> 34:20.516
-Thank you for seeing me.
-Anything for Isabella.

34:21.601 --> 34:23.561
This must be serious.

34:24.020 --> 34:26.355
Your friend and I are the only two here
who aren't drinking.

34:27.023 --> 34:28.941
Miguel Ángel worked
as a bodyguard for my uncle.

34:29.025 --> 34:30.693
He was the only one
who'd play with us kids.

34:31.235 --> 34:34.489
But only after his shift was done.
He's a serious man.

34:35.448 --> 34:38.576
Maybe he'll play with you now.
If you ask nicely.

34:40.745 --> 34:42.246
I'm here on business.

34:42.330 --> 34:43.247
Yes, I know.

34:44.749 --> 34:47.710
You want to move Sinaloan weed
through Tijuana

34:47.794 --> 34:49.921
using the Arellano Félix boys.

34:50.838 --> 34:52.090
[chuckles]

34:54.383 --> 34:56.469
[Toto's "Hold the Line" playing]

34:59.764 --> 35:02.600
♪ It's not in the way
